      • canChain

        public boolean canChain(Node node)
        Checks whether this Node can chain to the given node.
        Parameters:
        node - The Node we want to check.
        Returns:
        True if we can chain to the following node, false if we cannot.

      • chain

        public Node chain(Node nextNode)
        Chain to the given next Node. We save the given Node as our "next" node in the chain, and then return it.
        Parameters:
        nextNode - The next node to chain to.
        Returns:
        The Node to chain to.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If you try to chain to a node where canChain(Node) returns false.

      • getNextNode

        @Nullable
public Node getNextNode()
        Returns:
        The next Node in this chain, if there is one.

      • getPointer

        public ResourcePointer getPointer()
        Returns:
        The ResourcePointer that point to this Node's position in the resource. Useful for logging errors and whatnot.
